    "statement": "<p>Fafa has an array <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>A</i></span> of <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> positive integers, the function <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>f</i>(<i>A</i>)</span> is defined as <img align=\"middle\" class=\"tex-formula\" src=\"https://espresso.codeforces.com/0137b4d8cf93a90c358b762bd32038fce424a41e.png\" style=\"max-width: 100.0%;max-height: 100.0%;\"/>. He wants to do <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>q</i></span> queries of two types:</p><ul> <li> <span class=\"tex-span\">1\u2009<i>l</i>\u2009<i>r</i>\u2009<i>x</i></span> \u2014 find the maximum possible value of <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>f</i>(<i>A</i>)</span>, if <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>x</i></span> is to be added to one element in the range <span class=\"tex-span\">[<i>l</i>,\u2009\u2009<i>r</i>]</span>. You can choose to which element to add <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>x</i></span>. </li><li> <span class=\"tex-span\">2\u2009<i>l</i>\u2009<i>r</i>\u2009<i>x</i></span> \u2014 increase all the elements in the range <span class=\"tex-span\">[<i>l</i>,\u2009\u2009<i>r</i>]</span> by value <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>x</i></span>. </li></ul><p>Note that queries of type <span class=\"tex-span\">1</span> don't affect the array elements.</p>",
    "inputSpecification": "<p>The first line contains one integer <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> <span class=\"tex-span\">(3\u2009\u2264\u2009<i>n</i>\u2009\u2264\u200910<sup class=\"upper-index\">5</sup>)</span> \u2014 the length of the array.</p><p>The second line contains <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> positive integers <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">1</sub>,\u2009<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">2</sub>,\u2009...,\u2009<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>n</i></sub></span> <span class=\"tex-span\">(0\u2009&lt;\u2009<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>i</i></sub>\u2009\u2264\u200910<sup class=\"upper-index\">9</sup>)</span> \u2014 the array elements.</p><p>The third line contains an integer <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>q</i></span> <span class=\"tex-span\">(1\u2009\u2264\u2009<i>q</i>\u2009\u2264\u200910<sup class=\"upper-index\">5</sup>)</span> \u2014 the number of queries. </p><p>Then <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>q</i></span> lines follow, line <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>i</i></span> describes the <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>i</i></span>-th query and contains four integers <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>t</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>i</i></sub>\u2009<i>l</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>i</i></sub>\u2009<i>r</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>i</i></sub>\u2009<i>x</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>i</i></sub></span> <img align=\"middle\" class=\"tex-formula\" src=\"https://espresso.codeforces.com/4fb4806a3938928170dbc2d3de38824e94c8ed4a.png\" style=\"max-width: 100.0%;max-height: 100.0%;\"/>. </p><p>It is guaranteed that at least one of the queries is of type <span class=\"tex-span\">1</span>.</p>",
    "outputSpecification": "<p>For each query of type <span class=\"tex-span\">1</span>, print the answer to the query.</p>",
